  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 19 May 1927
---
Bitter experience has taught me that all temples are not houses of God. They
can be habitations of the devil. These places of worship have no value
unless the keeper is a good man of God. Temples, mosques, churches are
what man makes them to be.
